Anonymous Wed 13 Mar 2019 13:06:38 No.21860972 Report
Quoted By: >>21861015 >>21861057 >>21861116 >>21861212
>>21860695
I've always had an issue with bird races. If they're able to fly they'd have to have hollow bones which would make them weak in direct confrontations, or insane wingspans which would be very costly from an evolutionary perspective. Human-sized birds would also be very easy to spot from the ground, so they'd likely be nocturnal or carrion-eaters. You wouldn't be able to dive between trees to find small pray if you're the size of a human, or to sneak up on anything. It'd make more sense to put them near an ocean - preferably nesting on cliff sides - and subsist mostly of fish. A nomad lifestyle would probably be impossible unless you're willing to go "magic!" to explain how they evolved.

I like the idea of making them smaller and frailer than other anthro species. If they're as bulky and strong as everybody else, they're basically OP since they have a clear advantage over others, and the smaller size helps make their ability to lift off the ground seem more sensible. But yeah, they wouldn't be able to hunt quite like real birds of prey. They'd have to use their flight differently. Maybe the wings are mostly for travel during changing seasons, and once they hunt they get on the ground and stalk the old-fashioned way, only using the wings for an extra push when pouncing on prey.
